The paper discusses a caching strategy for improving transaction throughput and recovery time in database systems using flash memory as an extension to DRAM buffer. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the optimization of flash write and reduction of disk access, which falls under the category of cs.OS (Operating Systems). The caching strategy proposed in the paper also involves managing the cache replacement policy, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of flash memory for database recovery, which is related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
